<div class="app-card-container">
  <div class="card">
    <h1>A little about myself</h1>

    <hr>

    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-md-4">
        <%= image_tag "Profile.jpg", width: 300, alt: "Profile Image", class: 'profile-img' %>

        <div class="skills">
          <% @skills.each do |skill| %>
            <div class="skill">
              <h4><%= skill.title %></h4>
              <div class="progress">
                <div 
                  class="progress-bar progress-bar-striped bg-warning"
                  role="progressbar"
                  aria-valuenow="<%= skill.percent_utilized %>"
                  aria-valuemax="100"
                  style="width: <%= skill.percent_utilized %>%"
                ></div>
              </div>
            </div>
          <% end %>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="col-md-8">
        <p>I am a up and coming full stack developer based out of Utah. While going through the learning process, one of the main focus points was to take things step by step to ensure a streamlined process for the client and a finished product that will exceed expectations</p>

        <p>
          <button
            class="btn btn-primary"
            type="button"
            data-toggle="collapse"
            data-target="#jobHistory"
            aria-expanded="false"
            aria-controller="jobHistory"
          >
            Job History
          </button>

          <button
            class="btn btn-primary"
            type="button"
            data-toggle="collapse"
            data-target="#Education"
            aria-expanded="false"
            aria-controller="Education"
          >
            Education
          </button>
        </p>

        <p>
          <div class="collapse" id="jobHistory">
            <div class="card card-block">
              Job 1 (Change these)
            </div>
            <div class="card card-block">
              Job 2 (Change these)
            </div>
            <div class="card card-block">
              Job 3 (Change these)
            </div>
          </div>
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>